                            <comment id="66504" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 12 Sep 2013 15:35:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be fixed now that &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3669&quot; title=&quot;(mdt_xattr.c:178:mdt_getxattr()) ASSERTION( lu_object_assert_exists(&amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;mti_object-&amp;gt;mot_obj) ) failed:&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has been closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65593" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 3 Sep 2013 12:47:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3669&quot; title=&quot;(mdt_xattr.c:178:mdt_getxattr()) ASSERTION( lu_object_assert_exists(&amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;mti_object-&amp;gt;mot_obj) ) failed:&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7208/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7208/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64850" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2013 14:02:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This appears to be a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3713&quot; title=&quot;Failure on test suite sanity test_17k: get_xattr_names: llistxattr failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3713&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3713&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64615" author="jay" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2013 16:08:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There was no such information to indicate why reading acl access info failed. From the test case itself, I feel it&apos;s not necessary to use `cp -p&apos; so changing it to `cp&apos; would work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64601" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2013 13:52:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jinshan, as you already documented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3704&quot; title=&quot;sanity-hsm test_21 - test_24 Error: &amp;#39;could not release file&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3704&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3704&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, test_3 failures are due to ENODATA return during &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;cp -p /etc/passwd $TESTFILE.append || error &amp;quot;could not create file&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; command when trying to set &quot;system.posix_acl_access&quot; XATTR. But why are some XATTRs part of &quot;cp -p&quot; work ? And in any case we may just check that file content after copy is ok in the test ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64132" author="jamesanunez" created="Mon, 12 Aug 2013 23:17:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another failure at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/aa3d4616-001d-11e3-a856-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/aa3d4616-001d-11e3-a856-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
This one with ZFS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
